      <akn:section eId="sec_19_1308_14">
        <akn:num>19-1308.14</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Discretionary powers; tax savings.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_19-1308_14_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Notwithstanding the breadth of discretion granted to a trustee in the terms of the trust, including the use of such terms as “absolute”, “sole”, or “uncontrolled”, the trustee shall exercise a discretionary power in good faith and in accordance with the terms and purposes of the trust and the interests of the beneficiaries.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_19-1308_14_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Section 21-1722 applies to a trust governed by this chapter.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
